        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                <hi rend="underline">Monday</hi>&#44; Pericope<lb/> Chari&#44; <date>&#40;April&#41; 1854</date></p>
            <p>Peace&#44; etc. etc.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Sir&#58; I received your letter yester&#8211;<lb/>day and thank you many times for
                the<lb/> trouble you have taken for my sake. Forgive<lb/> me for the <del>enclosed</del>
                trouble and send me by return mail a<lb/> complete itemized bill&#44; so that I can
                look for the<lb/> goods. And I shall at once send you a check.<lb/> That is&#44; as
                much as I can spare. As soon as<lb/> I have regulated my affairs&#44; I shall pay
                the<lb/> full bill for the furniture. </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As regards the list of subscribers. I must<lb/> report that some of those who are on
                the list never<lb/> intended to order them bound. <persName>Mr. Mark<lb/>
                    Levy</persName> is the only one who wants to have them&#44; and<lb/> only
                because he wants to bless you to print it. In<lb/> a few weeks I will send you a
                list. I have en&#8211;<lb/>gaged a man who will canvass for
                subscrip&#8211;<lb/>tions. Your eternal friend&#44;<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon Cohen Noot</persName>.</p>

        </body>
    </text>
